ot\u011b\u0161ovcov\u00e1-Vesecky (1877-1952).png|center|thumb|171x171px|Anna Kot\u011b\u0161ovcov\u00e1-Vesecky (1877-1952)]]\n|-\n|27 September 1902\n[[SS Main (1900)|SS Main]]\n\nBremen[[File:S.S. Main.jpg|center|thumb|168x168px]]<br />\n|11 October 1902 (2:36 PM)\n[[Ellis Island|New York]]\n|Hanzlik - Josef (1872-) [with wife Marie and a married woman Helena Moutvic. He previously lived in Polanka]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:JF25-M4F|title=New York Passenger Arrival Lists (Ellis Island), 1892-1924|last=Hanzlik|first=|date=1902|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|4 December 1902\nSS Weimar\n\n[[Bremen]]\n|21 December 1902\n[[Baltimore]]\n|Koncal - Anna (1848-1938) [widow of Josef Picka from Mysliv, with 2 children from Milcice]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:2CSF-GKW|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Koncal|first=|date=1902|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nMares - Marie (1884-)\n|\n|-\n|12 February 1903\n[[SS Breslau (1901)|SS Breslau]]\n\n[[Bremen]][[File:USAT_Bridgeport_in_port,_circa_in_1946_(NH_98474).jpg|center|thumb|SS Breslau (converted to USAT Bridgeport)]]\n|28 February 1903\n[[Baltimore]]\n|Ticha - Anna (1851-1923) [wife of Vaclav Houdek from Mysliv, traveled with her son]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:2CSF-BNX|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Ticha|first=|date=1903|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nHoudek - Josef (1885-1962)\n|[[File:Anna Tichov\u00e1-Houdek (1851-1923).png|center|thumb|174x174px|Anna Tichov\u00e1-Houdek (1851-1923)]]\n|-\n|2 June 1903\n[[SS Kaiser Wilhelm der Grosse|SS Kaiser Wilhelm der Gro\u00dfe]]\n\n[[Bremen]][[File:SS Kaiser Wilhelm der Gro\u00dfe.png|center|thumb]]<br />\n|10 June 1903\n[[Ellis Island|New York]]\n|Paty - Anezka (